# PRAXIS GitLab main sync

**Remote:** `origin` → `https://labs.gauntletai.com/monicapeters/praxis.git`  
**Source of truth:** `main` on GitLab (`origin/main`). Dev work lives on feature branches (e.g. `monica/dashboard-human-gate`).

## When to sync

Run **before starting a work session** and **before opening a merge request**.

## Standard sync (on your dev branch)

```powershell
git fetch origin main
git merge origin/main
```

If `main` has moved, that brings those commits into your dev branch. If it's already current, Git will say "Already up to date."

## Agent behavior

When the user starts dashboard/knowledge/eval work or asks to open an MR:

1. Confirm the current branch is a **dev/feature branch**, not `main`.
2. Run `git fetch origin main` then `git merge origin/main` (use `;` between commands in PowerShell, not `&&`).
3. If merge conflicts occur, resolve **on the dev branch** only — never merge dev into `main` to sync.
4. Report: commits brought in from `main`, or "already up to date"; note any conflicts or unstaged WIP.

## Optional: refresh local `main` without checkout

```powershell
git fetch origin main:main
```

## Invariants

- Sync direction is always **`origin/main` → dev branch**, never dev → `main`.
- Publish dev work with `git push origin <dev-branch>`; open MRs with **target branch `main`**.
- Use `/sync-with-main` or the `sync-dev-with-gitlab-main` skill for the full checklist.
